refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public voidDs\Map::ksort callablecomparator
Sorts the map in-place by key, using an optional comparator function.

&reftitle.parameters;


   comparator



     &return.callbacksort;

     &callback.cmp;



      Returning non-integer values from the comparison
      function, such as float, will result in an internal cast to
      int of the callback's return value. So values such as
      0.99 and 0.1 will both be cast to an integer value of 0, which will
      compare such values as equal.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Ds\Map::ksort example


<?php
$map = new \Ds\Map(["b" => 2, "c" => 3, "a" => 1]);
$map->ksort();

print_r($map);
?>


   &example.outputs.similar;


Ds\Map Object
(
    [0] => Ds\Pair Object
        (
            [key] => a
            [value] => 1
        )

    [1] => Ds\Pair Object
        (
            [key] => b
            [value] => 2
        )

    [2] => Ds\Pair Object
        (
            [key] => c
            [value] => 3
        )

)




   Ds\Map::ksort example using a comparator


<?php
$map = new \Ds\Map([1 => "x", 2 => "y", 0 => "z"]);

// Reverse
$map->ksort(function($a, $b) {
    return $b <=> $a;
});

print_r($map);
?>


   &example.outputs.similar;


Ds\Map Object
Ds\Map Object
